&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re seeking an exceptional Senior Product Marketing Manager who will play a key role in shaping the narrative around our suite of tools designed for the modern creator. In this dynamic role, you’ll balance the positioning and messaging of individual features while crafting a cohesive, compelling story for Kit as a whole.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll dive deep into the diverse world of creators—from artists and bloggers to educators and entrepreneurs, uncovering their unique needs through customer research, data, and competitive insight. You’ll translate those insights into clear, differentiated messaging that resonates across the full spectrum of our audience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires a rare blend of &lt;strong&gt;strategic thinking, storytelling, and scrappy execution&lt;/strong&gt;. You know how to connect product capabilities to market opportunities, test and iterate quickly, and communicate with clarity—whether you&#39;re enabling a sales team, shaping a go-to-market plan, or influencing product direction. You thrive in cross-functional environments and bring others along with context and conviction. Join us and play a pivotal role in a team committed to empowering creators with tools that turn passion into livelihood—by telling the right stories, to the right people, at the right time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively gather insights from customer research, sales calls, data, and competitors to educate internal stakeholders and help inform product strategy, roadmap, pricing, and packaging.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead win/loss user research efforts and act as the voice of the creators we serve.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Positioning, messaging, and narrative design&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Refine our target personas and value propositions. Identify product use cases that enable creators to grow their audience, connect with their audiences, and earn a living online.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Iteratively improve our positioning and messaging so that it clearly communicates our product’s value. Distill complexity into crisp messaging&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help us define a new market category for the creator space and collaboratively shape a narrative that clearly communicates the value of our offerings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Planning and execution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage and improve our go-to-market playbooks and lead the execution of product launches, ongoing feature releases, and new partnerships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate and influence internal stakeholders, including Product, Marketing, Sales, and Support teams, to identify and support their unique needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create customer-facing material, including web copy, videos, emails, case studies, blog posts, FAQs, tutorials, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analysis&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Measure product marketing performance through key metrics such as revenue growth, conversion rates, monthly active users, and feature adoption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use large data sets to create high-confidence forecasts and growth plans to achieve company goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;The right candidate has&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Multiple years of in-house experience in product marketing for SaaS, B2C tech companies. B2B experience is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven understanding of segmentation strategies, developing buyer personas, articulating customer pain points, and crafting customer-facing messaging&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional visual, written, spoken communication, and presentation skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven Product-Led Growth (PLG) marketing experience with strong research and analytical skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting sales enablement through effective messaging, collateral, and tools that drive revenue and improve sales performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to work as a team player, confidently collaborate with senior executives, and build consensus among multiple stakeholders and teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to thrive in an ambiguous, fast-paced, and flexible environment with a high degree of autonomy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bias towards action and an operator mindset, with an understanding for the most important metrics and how to produce measurable results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated, organized, and communicative, capable of working effectively in a 100% remote work environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have enthusiasm and belief in our &lt;a href=&quot;https://convertkit.com/mission&quot;&gt;mission, vision, and values&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
